Course Scheduling

Authors: Jonathan Kelaty, Manal Zneit

This is a supplemental visualization tool for our CSCI 350/761 Artificial Intelligence final project. Our project addresses the problem of course scheduling for universities as a Constraint Satisfaction Problem. Our objective when designing the interface for this project was to create a tool that can be practically used using readily available information provided by any school. To use this tool, simply upload a CSV with course information and optionally a CSV containing instructor's preferences for certain scheduling parameters. Sample CSVs and templates can be found below.
